OL,4,G2200FBritish Art at War: Bomberg,
OL,5,     FSickert and Nash
OL,6,     GAndrew Graham-Dixon tells the
OL,7,     Gstory of artist Walter Sickert,
OL,8,     Gwho understood that the theatre
OL,9,     Gof war was not confined to the
OL,10,     Gtrenches.
OL,11,G2300FLisbon: Art Lovers' Guide
OL,12,     GJanina Ramirez and Alastair Sooke
OL,13,     Greveal Lisbon's fascinating
OL,14,     Ghistory through its cobbled
OL,15,     Gstreets, steep hills, picturesque
OL,16,     Gshoreline and cultural riches.
OL,17,G0000FArt That Made Us
OL,18,     GIn the 18th century, trade and
OL,19,     Gconquest funds an explosion of
OL,20,     Gcreativity, and art stirs a
OL,21,     Ggrowing social conscience.
